<br>
I agree that mages are the most powerful they have been from a offensive stand point. However the fact is alot of people in EQ do not have a clue. I am willing to say the vast majority of those that play are clueless. When they think lets get a damage class they think Monk or Rogue. That is really the major problem. We can out damage monks and the majority of rogues (even the uber ones), but alot of people don't understand that. So because they don't magicians spend alot of time LFG unless they are popular and have alot of friends.  Perception is a huge thing in EQ because it is so community based. Until the perception that rogues/monks are the best damage classes in the game fades, mages will continue to have problems getting into highend guilds, and group finding.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>4) WHO CARES ABOUT QUADDERS!<br>
Only thing that bugs me is when the morons quad over other folks. Other folk get xp and levels skills, GOOD FOR THEM! Doesnt hurt mages, if wizzy pals get good things I'm happy.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't think anyone cares that druids/wizards can quad. I think what you are choosing to overlook is the fact that post 60 mages can no longer solo. However........Shamans, Druids, Wizards, Beastlords, Enchanters, Necros, and Bards are still off soloing. Those classes retained that core ability while mages lost it. Just because you are ok with it doesn't mean that everyone should feel as you do. If you are happy fine but why bitch at those that are not pleased with the fact they can no longer solo?<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>5) YES SOME THINGS STILL NEED FIXED.<br>
Servant of Ro for example, but in the most part, mages have come out shining.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I agree with that. Majority of the AA skills are nice. Servant of Ro needs a complete overhaul. It isn't working as intended and I fear even if it did it would suck. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>6) SUPPORT FRIENDS AND GOOD GUILDS<br>
This is crucuial, it's at the core of enjoyable gaming, nto only do friends and guilds help you, YOU MUST HELP THEM! You end up in a crappy guild cause you didnt support your old good one and it fell apart well thats partially YOUR FAULT. Help at events, arrange events, lead them etc.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I agree with this in part. However you have to understand that just like in real life you have to sometimes move on from a job that is going no where. Same goes for EQ, people leave guilds because they want better, and there is nothing wrong with that.<br>
<br>
I am very happy with the mage class. I still solo when I am bored in UP pretty well. To much down time for me right now because I don't have alot of the new skills because I am still getting old ones but I think once I get some more aa under my belt I will be able to atleast get experience in aa as fast as I did before PoP.<br>
<br>
The soloing thing doesn't really bother me but I do understand how some mages feel. I just think people need to understand that it is ok to have a different view point. You are ranting at people because they don't think being able to not solo, and LFG for hours is fun. You have alot of friends in game that is great but everyone doesn't. Honestly I don't have much time to solo because I am being asked to group with friend so much. However alot of people play at different times and are not as lucky as I am. You need to respect that, just as you want people to respect your point of view.<br>
<br>
Wezloc<br>
